fields.item_review: Bad writing, characters being out of behaviors. The art style is different, not necessarily bad, but the fighting scene is noticably terrible.
Good villain, bad writing in general. Characters having only one personality, and there is a lot of 'comedy'. Even in serious moments, they always try to put a joke or two to the scene.
Spectacular animation with incredible sounds. Good character depth, the story conceptually very simple but with added depth.
Really good animation and fight scenes. The story is mostly okay, with a cliffhanger at the end.

fields.item_title: El Camino: A Breaking Bad Movie
fields.item_review: A sequal to an amazing show. It gives the aftermath of a character having to deal with crimes that they did.

fields.item_title: Nanatsu no Taizai Movie 2: Hikari ni Norowareshi Mono-tachi
fields.item_review: Generic storyline, with an already developed characaters if you watched the anime. Decent animation and sound.

fields.item_title: The Conjuring: The Devil Made Me Do It
fields.item_review: Different kind of movie from your typical horror movies. Decent story, and decent characters. The movie always have an eerie feeling on every scene.

fields.item_title: Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace
fields.item_review: Pretty good movie overall. Decent characters, and an alright storyline
It is an epic conclusion to a decade plus storyline. Really good animation and final fight scene. Decent enough plot, but with a twist.

fields.item_title: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
fields.item_review: Amazing production that got put into making this movie. Captivating story and a really wide world building.
